23/07/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- At a news conference Thursday (22 July), Romania's chief negotiator with the EU, Vasile Puscas, said his country is determined to complete EU accession talks by the end of this year.
He described the latest statements by the European Commission and the Dutch presidency of the EU as very encouraging, and suggested negotiations might be finalised before November.
Romania must close talks on five remaining chapters out of a total of 31.
In other news, German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder and a delegation of business leaders plan to visit Bucharest in August.
Officials say the visit will serve as an expression of support for Romania's EU membership bid.
(Rompres, Mediafax - 22/07/04)
